          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Image Edit Requests"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When processing requests, validate input images for format and size limits (e.g., max 4096x4096 pixels). Parse edit prompts to extract key operations, and return structured responses with edited image URLs or base64 data. Implement retry logic for transient failures and log errors for debugging."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimizing Latency and Resource Usage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimize performance by batching multiple edit requests, leveraging GPU acceleration if available, and caching frequent edits. Monitor metrics like inference time and memory usage to adjust resource allocation. For high traffic, consider load balancing across multiple model instances."
